Revision history for Perl extension Dir::Project.

The contributors that suggested a given feature are shown in [].  [by ...]
indicates the contributor was also the author of the fix; Thanks!

* Dir::Project 3.022 2010/01/02

***	If symlinked to project_which, resolve paths.  [Brad Dobbie]

* Dir::Project 3.021 2010/08/04

****	Give obvious error message when MS-Windows unsupported.

* Dir::Project 3.020 2010/04/22

***	Add project_bin --run option.  [Craig Barner]

****	Fix Pod::Usage dependency, rt51024.  [Andreas Koenig]

* Dir::Project 3.017 2010/01/12

***	Added contrib/dir-project.el.

* Dir::Project 3.016 2009/07/13

****	Fix test failures when cwd contains spaces. [Bhavin Patel]

* Dir::Project 3.015 2009/06/24

****	Fix project_dir.mk to allow globally installed project_dir programs.
	The path may be changed with the new DIRPROJECT_PROJECTDIREXE variable.

* Dir::Project 3.014 2009/05/29

****	Fix t/03_spaces.t failure.  [Sebastian Knapp]

* Dir::Project 3.013 2009/05/08

**	This package is now licensed under LGPL v3 and/or Artistic v2.0.

* Dir::Project 3.012 2008/06/10

****	Documentation updates.

* Dir::Project 3.011 2007/07/05

***	Remove use of DIRPROJECT_PREFIX in make install.  [Joel Martin]
	The Makefile now uses INSTALLLIB as the location for installing
	makefiles to more closely match the Perl standard; you may need
	to change this variable, or PREFIX to install globally.

* Dir::Project 3.010 2007/04/24

***	Allow DIRPROJECT_PATH to include absolute directories. [Bryce Denney]

***	Removed unused $Dir::Project::Set_Defaults variable.

* Dir::Project 3.002 2007/04/05

****	Fix 'make test' issues on non-Linux systems.  [cpan-testers]

* Dir::Project 3.001 2007/04/03

****	Fix --help to use Pod::Usage instead of depreciated pod2text.

* Dir::Project 3.000 2006/07/14

**	First public release.  (Has been internal-use for 5 years.)

